      "content": "It is completely understandable why the vastness of existence and eventual decay can lead to feelings of futility. When confronting such enormous perspectives, it can feel impossible to find a reason to persevere. Perhaps the focus needs to shift from a grand, all-encompassing meaning to finding small, immediate moments of subjective value. Even in the face of impermanence, the experience of connection or beauty can hold meaning for you right now.",
      "source": "target",
